<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idaaf8ab03-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s7562"><num value="7562">§ 7562.</num><heading> Clothing</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President may prescribe the quantity and kind of clothing to be issued annually to members of the Army.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idaaf8ab04-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(<ref href="/us/act/1956-08-10/ch1041">Aug. 10, 1956, ch. 1041</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/70A/256">70A Stat. 256</ref>, § 4562; renumbered § 7562, <ref href="/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s808/d">Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 808(d)</ref>, <date date="2018-08-13">Aug. 13, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/1839">132 Stat. 1839</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
